safe with him. Your ice cream is not.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:957;s:5:\"image\";s:68:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/gideon-1.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:12:\"Race Support\";}i:2;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Nick Collins\";s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Viscount\";s:7:\"contact\";s:35:\"members@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\";s:11:\"description\";s:258:\"Originally from Europe, Nick has lived in Crown Heights since 2009. Aspiring long distance runner, Nicks first race was the Brooklyn half in 2015. In addition to running, Nick can be found regularly at the spin studio, at bikram yoga and circuit training.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:604;s:5:\"image\";s:64:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/Nick.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:10:\"Membership\";}i:3;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"Elly Kuhlman\";s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Viscount\";s:7:\"contact\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:218:\"Elly moved to Crown Heights last year after seven years in the midwest. Since then, she has enjoyed eating (and running) her way around Brooklyn. She hopes to someday remain uninjured long enough to run a marathon.\r\n\r\n\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:927;s:5:\"image\";s:64:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/elly.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:10:\"Membership\";}i:4;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"Liz Chen\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Safety Squire\";s:7:\"contact\";s:31:\"run@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\";s:11:\"description\";s:269:\"Liz moved to Crown Heights from Nashville, where she started running in 2014 through a couch to 5k group. She ran her first half marathon in 2015, and now leads our beginners run.\r\n\r\nAn employment lawyer by day, she enjoys playing her mandolin and eating all the tacos.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:246;s:5:\"image\";s:78:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/image_6247086656-1.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:21:\"Leader of Run Leaders\";}i:5;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:13:\"Megann Rogers\";s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Baronness of Noble Courts\";s:7:\"contact\";s:34:\"events@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:1164;s:5:\"image\";s:87:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2017/02/megannbanana-e1487616750619.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:6:\"Events\";}i:6;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:11:\"Aliza Gazek\";s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Cardinal of Community Connection\";s:7:\"contact\";s:37:\"community@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\";s:11:\"description\";s:305:\"Aliza ran her first half marathon in San Francisco with two goals: run the whole time, and make a new friend. Shes kept up both as she moved from the Bay Area to Brooklyn.\r\n\r\nAliza also loves cooking and composting, dressing up in wacky costumes, sending snail mail and eavesdropping all over the city.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:206;s:5:\"image\";s:65:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/aliza.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:9:\"Community\";}i:7;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:17:\"Spencer McCormick\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Lord Webmaster\";s:7:\"contact\";s:16:\"spnzrr@gmail.com\";s:11:\"description\";s:305:\"A simple commoner who lives in a shed surrounded by chickens, Spencer is supremely honored to serve in her Majesty\'s Royal Council.\r\n\r\nSpencer runs often. In 2010 he ran his one and only marathon with a live streaming camera hat (see photo). He occasionally runs ultras and once he bicycled across Africa.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:322;s:5:\"image\";s:108:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/73402_10100129682387259_3222231_n-e1447085635198.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:4:\"Tech\";}i:8;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:17:\"Stephanie Butikis\";s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Proprieter of Ye Olde Gear Shoppe\";s:7:\"contact\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:383:\"Stephanie is originally from Philadelphia. She has run 3 marathons: in South Korea and in Philadelphia in 2013, and in New Jersey in 2016 (where she ran a second Boston qualifying time).\r\n\r\nShe enjoys running in the elements, drawing, ice cream, and in free time, making custom silkscreen gear for CHRC! Visit her website for her portfolio and more information about custom projects.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:37;s:5:\"image\";s:77:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/Stephanie-Butikis.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:11:\"Merchandise\";}i:9;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:11:\"Nate Turner\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Duke of Design\";s:7:\"contact\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:1612;s:5:\"image\";s:108:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/13055166_10154176877756522_8216620066358185759_o.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:18:\"Merchandise Design\";}i:10;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:21:\"Kristen Kainer-Turner\";s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Duchess of Road Runners\";s:7:\"contact\";s:36:\"external@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\";s:11:\"description\";s:288:\"Kristen has been running longer than some of her clubmates have been alive, but she didnt run her first half marathon until 2013.\r\n\r\nShe moved away from New York for a number of years, but is ever so happy to be back home. Her cats are named after Meb Keflezighi and Katherine Switzer.\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:926;s:5:\"image\";s:69:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/kristen-1.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:12:\"NYRR Liaison\";}i:11;a:6:{s:4:\"name\";s:15:\"Sunny Kasabwala\";s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Jester of Many Hats\";s:11:\"description\";s:267:\"Sunny loves to hike and camp, has tales of adventure to share on any run. \r\nSunny contributes to the council by contributing his many talents encompassing the roles of treasurer, managing our Instagram account, and taking club members out on hiking and camping trips!\";s:8:\"image_id\";i:955;s:5:\"image\";s:67:\"https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/app/uploads/2015/08/sunny-1.jpg\";s:12:\"imagecaption\";s:29:\"Treasurer/SocialMedia/Camping\";}}'),(4728,36,'_edit_lock','1492632052:2'),(4729,36,'_edit_last','2'),(4730,36,'_wp_attachment_backup_sizes','a:3:{s:9:\"full-orig\";a:3:{s:5:\"width\";