ed','closed','','1439-revision-v1','','','2017-04-17 05:04:26','2017-04-17 05:04:26','',1439,'https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/1439-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1441,2,'2017-04-17 05:06:58','2017-04-17 05:06:58','Crown Heights Running Club embraces the diversity of our members and the breadth of our neighborhood. We wantto bring neighbors and runners together ina fun, safe, and inclusive community while supporting each member reach their goals through group runs, social events, and volunteering.\r\n\r\nOur group is made up of all paces and experience levels - we believe that every runner has something to offer. Our vision is for members to meet friends and running buddies; train together; to share ourstrengths and resources. Let\'sexplore all that Crown Heights has to offer!To become a member of the #RunningRoyalty, <a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/l8nNHAukXEcBhDwo1\" target=\"_blank\">contact us </a>today!\r\n<div class=\"pacers\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1\">The Royal Council</h2>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half\">\r\n<h3><small>Vaunted Guardian o\' the Banner</small>\r\nGideon Bautista</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-957 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/gideon-1-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Race Rally Lead</em>\r\n\r\nGideon Bautista wants to run with you because a conversational pace makes the workout go by so much faster.\r\n\r\nBorn in NY, raised in RI, and educated in Boston, he is an actor-writer, but your story is safe with him. Your ice cream is not.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half\">\r\n<h3><small>Queen of CHRC-landia</small>\r\nKay Naito</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-535 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/IMG_9446-1-e1456963975198-129x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"129\" height=\"150\" /><em>Club Main Contact</em>\r\n\r\nKay grew up in Canada where she was inspired at a young age by Terry Fox. She ran varsity in high school and college, coached and led teams in nordic ski, dragon-boat racing and ultimate frisbee.\r\n\r\nKay committed to running a marathon a year in her 30s and plans to run ultras in her 40s.She enjoys yoga, reading, traveling and exploring Brooklyn with friends.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:contact@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\">contact@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Proprieter of Ye Olde Gear Shoppe</small>\r\nStephanie Butikis</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-37 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/Stephanie-Butikis-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Merchandiser</em>\r\n\r\nStephanie is originally from Philadelphia. She has run 3 marathons: in South Korea and in Philadelphia in 2013, and in New Jersey in 2016 (where she ran a second Boston qualifying time).\r\n\r\nShe enjoys running in the elements, drawing, ice cream, and in free time, making custom silkscreen gear for CHRC! Visit her <a href=\"http://www.stephaniebutikis.com/\">website</a> for her portfolio and more information about custom projects.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Lord Webmaster</small>\r\nSpencer McCormick</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-322\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/73402_10100129682387259_3222231_n-e1447085635198-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"73402_10100129682387259_3222231_n\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Webmaster</em>\r\n\r\nA simple commoner who lives in a shed surrounded by chickens, Spencer is supremely honored to serve in her Majesty\'s Royal Council.\r\n\r\nSpencer runs often and races rarely. In 2010 he ran his one and only marathon with a live streaming camera hat (see photo). He occasionally runs ultras and once he <a href=\"http://toaddis.com\">bicycled across Africa</a>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:webmaster@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\">webmaster@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Baron ofTwittergram</small>\r\nSunny Kasabwala</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-955 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/sunny-1-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Social Media and Camping Manager</em>\r\n\r\nSunnyloves to hike and camp, has tales of adventure to share on any run. In addition to managing our Instagram account, Sunnyhelps to organize camping and hiking trips for his fellow royalty.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Trusted Viscounts</small>\r\nNick Collins and Elly Kuhlman</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-604 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/Nick-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Membership Coordinators</em>\r\n\r\nOriginally from Europe, Nick has lived in Crown Heights since 2009. Aspiring long distance runner, Nicks first race was the Brooklyn half in 2015. In addition to running, Nick can be found regularly at the spin studio, at bikram yoga and circuit training.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright wp-image-920 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/elly-150x150.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Elly moved to Crown Heights last year after seven years in the midwest. Since then, she has enjoyed eating (and running) her way around Brooklyn. She hopes to someday remain uninjured long enough to run a marathon.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:members@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\" target=\"_blank\">members@<span class=\"il\">crownheightsrunningclub</span>.<span class=\"il\">nyc</span></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Duchess ofRoad Runners</small>\r\nKristen Kainer-Turner</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-926 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/kristen-1-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>NYRR Liaison</em>\r\n\r\nKristen has been running longer than some of her clubmates have been alive, but she didnt run her first half marathon until 2013.\r\n\r\nShe moved away from New York for a number of years, but is ever so happy to be back home. Her cats are named after Meb Keflezighi and Katherine Switzer.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half\">\r\n<h3><small>Royal Council Member</small>\r\nTHIS COULD BE YOU</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-425 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/12/Screen-Shot-2015-12-13-at-7.22.06-AM-150x150.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />THIS COULD BE YOU\r\n\r\nWant to lead runs or be a part of the Council? <a href=\"mailto:runningroyalty01@gmail.com\">Get in touch</a>!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class=\"h1\">COMMITTEE LEADERS</h2>\r\nAll Members are encouraged and welcome to join a committee. If you would like to join, please<a href=\"mailto:runningroyalty01@gmail.com\">Get in touch</a>!\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Safety Squire</small>\r\nLiz Chen</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-246\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/image_6247086656-1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"liz chen\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Leader ofRun Leaders</em>\r\n\r\nLiz moved to Crown Heights from Nashville, where she started running in 2014 through a couch to 5k group. She ran her first half marathon in 2015, and now leads our beginners run.\r\n\r\nAn employment lawyer by day, she enjoys playing her mandolin and eating all the tacos.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"mailto:run@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc\">run@crownheightsrunningclub.nyc</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half clearfix\">\r\n<h3><small>Baronness of Noble Courts</small>\r\nMegann Rogers</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-927 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/elly-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><i>Events Coordinator</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"half\">\r\n<h3><small>Cardinal of Community Connection</small>\r\nAliza Gazek</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-245 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2015/08/FullSizeRender-e1443654289607-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><em>Community Engagement Coordinator</em>\r\n\r\nAliza ran her first half marathon in San Francisco with two goals: run the whole time, and make a new friend. Shes kept up both as she moved from the Bay Area to Brooklyn.\r\n\r\nAliza also loves cooking and composting, dressing up in wacky costumes, sending snail mail and eavesdropping all over the city.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"half\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','8-revision-v1','','','2017-04-17 05:06:58','2017-04-17 05:06:58','',8,'https://crownheightsrunningclub.nyc/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1442,2,'2017-04-17 05:20:11','2017-04-17 05:20:11','Crown Heights Running Club embraces the diversity of our members and the breadth of our neighborhood. We wantto bring neighbors and runners together ina fun, safe, and inclusive community while supporting each member reach their goals through group runs, social events, and volunteering.\r\n\r\nOur group is made up of all paces and experience levels - we believe that every runner has something to offer. Our vision is for members to meet friends and running buddies; train together; to share ourstrengths and resources. Let\'sexplore all that Crown Heights has to offer!To become a member of the #RunningRoyalty, <a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/l8nNHAukXEcBhDwo1\" target=\"_blank\">contact us </a>today!\r\n<div cla